    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Order containing a single extant family, Struthionidae, containing the ostriches. Formerly believed to contain up to ten species in six families, DNA comparison has altered the classification in the 2000s.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
